   <abstract lang="eng">An atlas of atmospheric absorption calculations is presented for a vertical path through the atmosphere above altitudes of 4, 14, 30, 40, 45, and 54 km. The calculations are made with spectral resolutions of 0.1, 5, and 20 cm-l for the spectral region from 1 to 2600 cm-l. A discussion of the accuracy of the results is presented.</abstract>
